      <h2>What Is a Flame Diffuser, Anyway?</h2>

      <p>A flame diffuser is a hybrid device combining three separate functions:</p>

      <ol>
        <li><strong>Essential oil diffusion:</strong> Uses ultrasonic vibration to break down essential oils into a fine mist. Unlike heat diffusers, ultrasonic diffusion doesn't damage the oils' aromatic compounds.</li>
        <li><strong>Humidification:</strong> That same mist saturates the air, raising humidity levels. This is particularly beneficial in dry winters or air-conditioned spaces.</li>
        <li><strong>Ambient lighting:</strong> LED lights (usually RGB) create a flame-like effect or color-changing glow. This is purely aesthetic but creates the "ambiance" value proposition.</li>
      </ol>

      <p>The FlameFusion does all three, but doesn't excel equally at each. The flame effect is its strongest feature, followed by humidification, with scent throw being its weakest point.</p>

