        <li>Charge the device fully via USB-C (approximately 2–3 hours for first charge)</li>
        <li>Fill the 300ml reservoir with distilled or demineralized water (tap water can leave mineral deposits)</li>
        <li>Add 3–5 drops of your chosen essential oil to the water</li>
        <li>Reassemble the tank and place on a level, non-flammable surface</li>
        <li>Power on and select your preferred mist and light modes</li>
      </ol>

      <h3>Best Practices</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Oil choice matters:</strong> Use high-quality, pure essential oils. Cheaper oils often have weak scent profiles, making the diffuser seem ineffective.</li>
        <li><strong>Placement:</strong> Position on a nightstand, desk, or low shelf 2–4 feet from where you'll be sitting/sleeping. This optimizes both visual impact and scent reach.</li>
        <li><strong>Water quality:</strong> Distilled water prevents mineral buildup and keeps the ultrasonic atomizer clean longer.</li>
        <li><strong>Oil count:</strong> Don't exceed 5 drops per tank fill. More oil doesn't equal better scent; it can clog the atomizer.</li>
        <li><strong>Mist mode selection:</strong> Use continuous mist for humidity-focused sessions (especially winter). Use intermittent modes (30 min or 1 hour) for scenting without over-humidifying.</li>
        <li><strong>Light mode for bedroom:</strong> Set to the dimmest brightness and choose a single color (not cycling) to avoid sleep disruption.</li>
        <li><strong>Maintenance:</strong> Empty the tank after 1–2 days of non-use to prevent stagnant water and mold growth.</li>
      </ul>

