      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

      <div class="faq">
        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-question">Can I use regular tap water, or does it have to be distilled?</div>
          <div class="faq-answer">You can use tap water, but distilled or demineralized water is strongly recommended. Tap water contains minerals that build up on the ultrasonic atomizer, reducing efficiency over time and potentially creating white dust buildup in your room. If you use tap water, you'll need to clean the atomizer monthly instead of every 3–4 months.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-question">How long does the flame effect actually look realistic?</div>
          <div class="faq-answer">From 3+ feet away, the flame effect is very convincing—about 8/10 for realism. Up close, you'll notice it's an LED pattern. In dim lighting (bedroom or evening use), it looks nearly lifelike. In bright daylight, it's more obviously artificial. This is true for most LED flame diffusers at this price point.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-question">Will the scent spread throughout my bedroom?</div>
          <div class="faq-answer">The scent reach is 6–8 feet max. In a typical bedroom, if you place the diffuser on a nightstand, you'll smell it while in bed but not strongly at the far side of the room. For whole-room scenting, you'd need a larger capacity diffuser or multiple units. High-quality, pure essential oils have better scent throw than budget oils.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-question">Is it safe to run overnight in the bedroom?</div>
          <div class="faq-answer">Yes. The FlameFusion is quiet (25 dB), has an auto shut-off when water runs out, and doesn't produce heat. Set the light to the dimmest setting and choose a single color (not cycling mode) to avoid sleep disruption. Empty the tank after a few hours of overnight use to prevent stagnant water.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-question">What essential oils work best in this diffuser?</div>
          <div class="faq-answer">Lavender, peppermint, eucalyptus, and chamomile are all excellent choices. Avoid overly thick oils (like thick frankincense) as they can clog the ultrasonic plate. Always use 100% pure essential oils—diluted or synthetic fragrances won't provide real aromatherapy benefits. Never use fragrance oils or carrier oils.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-question">How often do I need to clean it?</div>
          <div class="faq-answer">If you use distilled water, a deep clean every 3–4 months is sufficient. Empty and rinse the tank after 1–2 days of non-use. If you use tap water, plan for monthly cleaning of the ultrasonic atomizer. Over time, essential oil residue can accumulate, reducing mist output.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-question">Can I use it without essential oils, just for humidification?</div>
          <div class="faq-answer">Absolutely. Fill it with plain distilled water and run it in continuous mist mode. You'll get the humidification benefit and the visual flame effect, just without scent. This is actually a great setup for allergic individuals or those who prefer no fragrance.</div>
        </div>
      </div>

